#. Tag: para
#: hardening.xml:4021
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting with the 2.6.x kernel releases, Linux offers <emphasis>Address "
"Space Layout Randomization</emphasis> (ASLR) and the <emphasis>No-eXecute</"
"emphasis> (NX bit) for mitigation of buffer overflow attacks. For more "
"information, see:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: hardening.xml:4044
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since version 12, &productname; already comes with some buffer overflow "
"attack mitigation techniques being enabled by default."
